    {
      "title": "Summary of Weak Verb Types",
      "titleArabic": "ملخص أنواع الأفعال الضعيفة",
      "content": [
        "Review the six types of weak verbs studied in Book 2."
      ],
      "keyPoints": [
        "مهموز (Hamzated): Has hamza as a radical - أَكَلَ، سَأَلَ، قَرَأَ",
        "مثال (Assimilated): و or ي as first radical - وَعَدَ، وَجَدَ",
        "أجوف (Hollow): و or ي as middle radical - قَالَ، زَارَ، نَامَ",
        "ناقص (Defective): و or ي as final radical - دَعَا، رَمَى، مَشَى",
        "مضعف (Doubled): Identical 2nd and 3rd radicals - مَدَّ، رَدَّ",
        "لفيف (Doubly Weak): Two weak radicals - وَفَى، طَوَى"
      ],
      "examples": [
